Facts –
  •	Unix has separate group and user management.
  o	Users are managed in /etc/passwd and Groups are managed in /etc/groups
    •	However, in out case the management happens through nsswitch.conf (nss stands for “name service switch)
  o	It has keys for psswd and groups that have the value “file ldap”
  o	These files can be looked-up in  /etc/openldap/ldap.conf
    •	The groups that can access the machine are defined in /etc/security/access.conf
  o	Format of adding entry is permission:user/groups:origin
